public class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        // The approach is to use logarithms. If log3(n) is an integer, then n is a power of three.
        // However, we cannot directly use log base 3 in Java, so we change the base using the
        // change of base formula: log3(n) = log10(n) / log10(3)
        // We need to check if the result of this division is an integer.

